                <h1>Discovering Jewish History: A Journey Through Time</h1>
                <p>Jewish history spans over 3,000 years, beginning with the biblical patriarchs. It encompasses the ancient kingdoms of Israel and Judah, the Babylonian exile, and the rise of rabbinic Judaism. The Jewish diaspora has profoundly influenced global culture, culminating in both tragedies, like the Holocaust, and cultural flourishing in modern times.</p>
